#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn22.87"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.87:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:0.2"
msgid "9. Theravagga "
msgstr "9. Senior Mendicants "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.87:0.3"
msgid "87. Vakkalisutta "
msgstr "87. With Vakkali "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn22.87:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā vakkali kumbhakāranivesane viharati ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno. "
msgstr "Now at that time Venerable Vakkali was staying in a potter’s shed, and he was sick, suffering, gravely ill. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā vakkali upaṭṭhāke āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then he addressed his carers, "

msgctxt "sn22.87:1.4"
msgid "“etha tumhe, āvuso, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamatha; upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vandatha: "
msgstr "“Please, reverends, go to the Buddha, and in my name bow with your head to his feet. Say to him: "

msgctxt "sn22.87:1.5"
msgid "‘vakkali, bhante, bhikkhu ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno, so bhagavato pāde sirasā vandatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Sir, the mendicant Vakkali is sick, suffering, and gravely ill. He bows with his head to your feet.’ "

msgctxt "sn22.87:1.6"
msgid "Evañca vadetha: "
msgstr "And then say: "

msgctxt "sn22.87:1.7"
msgid "‘sādhu kira, bhante, bhagavā yena vakkali bhikkhu tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā’”ti. "
msgstr "‘Sir, please go to the mendicant Vakkali out of compassion.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:1.8"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato vakkalissa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” those monks replied. They did as he asked. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:1.9"
msgid "“vakkali, bhante, bhikkhu ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno, so bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:1.10"
msgid "evañca pana vadeti: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:1.11"
msgid "‘sādhu kira, bhante, bhagavā yena vakkali bhikkhu tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:1.12"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena. "
msgstr "The Buddha consented in silence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.120, sc2
msgctxt "sn22.87:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yenāyasmā vakkali tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha robed up and, taking his bowl and robes, went to Venerable Vakkali. "

#. VAR: mañcake → mañcena (bj)
#. VAR: samadhosi → samañcosi (bj) | samañcopi (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn22.87:2.2"
msgid "Addasā kho āyasmā vakkali bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ. Disvāna mañcake samadhosi. "
msgstr "Venerable Vakkali saw the Buddha coming off in the distance and tried to rise on his cot. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:2.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ vakkaliṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "But the Buddha said to him, "

msgctxt "sn22.87:2.4"
msgid "“alaṃ, vakkali, mā tvaṃ mañcake samadhosi. "
msgstr "“It’s all right, Vakkali, don’t get up. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:2.5"
msgid "Santimāni āsanāni paññattāni; tatthāhaṃ nisīdissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "There are some seats spread out, I will sit there.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:2.6"
msgid "Nisīdi bhagavā paññatte āsane. Nisajja kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ vakkaliṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He sat on the seat spread out and said to Vakkali, "

msgctxt "sn22.87:2.7"
msgid "“kacci te, vakkali, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyaṃ, kacci dukkhā vedanā paṭikkamanti, no abhikkamanti; paṭikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no abhikkamo”ti? "
msgstr "“Vakkali, I hope you’re keeping well; I hope you’re alright. And I hope the pain is fading, not growing, that its fading is evident, not its growing.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:2.8"
msgid "“Na me, bhante, khamanīyaṃ, na yāpanīyaṃ; bāḷhā me dukkhā vedanā abhikkamanti, no paṭikkamanti; abhikkamosānaṃ paññāyati, no paṭikkamo”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, I’m not all right, I’m not getting by. My pain is terrible and growing, not fading; its growing is apparent, not its fading.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:2.9"
msgid "“Kacci te, vakkali, na kiñci kukkuccaṃ, na koci vippaṭisāro”ti? "
msgstr "“I hope you don’t have any remorse or regret?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:2.10"
msgid "“Taggha me, bhante, anappakaṃ kukkuccaṃ, anappako vippaṭisāro”ti. "
msgstr "“Indeed, sir, I have no little remorse and regret.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:2.11"
msgid "“Kacci pana taṃ, vakkali, attā sīlato na upavadatī”ti? "
msgstr "“I hope you have no reason to blame yourself when it comes to ethical conduct?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:2.12"
msgid "“Na kho maṃ, bhante, attā sīlato upavadatī”ti. "
msgstr "“No sir, I have no reason to blame myself when it comes to ethical conduct.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:2.13"
msgid "“No ce kira taṃ, vakkali, attā sīlato upavadati; atha kiñca te kukkuccaṃ ko ca vippaṭisāro”ti? "
msgstr "“In that case, Vakkali, why do you have remorse and regret?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: yāvatāhaṃ → yāhaṃ (si) | yāyāhaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "sn22.87:2.14"
msgid "“Cirapaṭikāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamitukāmo, natthi ca me kāyasmiṃ tāvatikā balamattā, yāvatāhaṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkameyyan”ti. "
msgstr "“For a long time I’ve wanted to go and see the Buddha, but I was physically too weak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn22.87:3.1"
msgid "“Alaṃ, vakkali, kiṃ te iminā pūtikāyena diṭṭhena? "
msgstr "“Enough, Vakkali! Why would you want to see this rotten body? "

msgctxt "sn22.87:3.2"
msgid "Yo kho, vakkali, dhammaṃ passati so maṃ passati; "
msgstr "One who sees the teaching sees me. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:3.3"
msgid "yo maṃ passati so dhammaṃ passati. "
msgstr "One who sees me sees the teaching. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:3.4"
msgid "Dhammañhi, vakkali, passanto maṃ passati; "
msgstr "Seeing the teaching, you see me. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:3.5"
msgid "maṃ passanto dhammaṃ passati. "
msgstr "Seeing me, you see the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.121, sc4
msgctxt "sn22.87:4.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, vakkali, "
msgstr "What do you think, Vakkali? "

msgctxt "sn22.87:4.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:4.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:4.4"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:4.5"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:4.6"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ: "
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be regarded thus: "

msgctxt "sn22.87:4.7"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:4.8"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:4.9"
msgid "“Vedanā … "
msgstr "“Is feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.87:4.10"
msgid "saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.87:4.11"
msgid "saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.87:4.12"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:4.13"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe … "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” … "

msgctxt "sn22.87:4.14"
msgid "eso me attāti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:4.15"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:4.16"
msgid "“Tasmātiha … pe … "
msgstr "“So you should truly see … "

msgctxt "sn22.87:4.17"
msgid "evaṃ passaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "Seeing this … "

msgctxt "sn22.87:4.18"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānātī”ti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn22.87:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ vakkaliṃ iminā ovādena ovaditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena gijjhakūṭo pabbato tena pakkāmi. "
msgstr "And then, after giving Venerable Vakkali this advice, the Buddha got up from his seat and went to the Vulture’s Peak Mountain. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:5.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā vakkali acirapakkantassa bhagavato upaṭṭhāke āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Vakkali addressed his carers, "

msgctxt "sn22.87:5.3"
msgid "“etha maṃ, āvuso, mañcakaṃ āropetvā yena isigilipassaṃ kāḷasilā tenupasaṅkamatha. "
msgstr "“Come on, reverends, lift my cot and take me to the Black Rock on the slopes of Isigili. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:5.4"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma mādiso antaraghare kālaṃ kattabbaṃ maññeyyā”ti? "
msgstr "It’s unthinkable for one like me to die in an inhabited area!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:5.5"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato vakkalissa paṭissutvā āyasmantaṃ vakkaliṃ mañcakaṃ āropetvā yena isigilipassaṃ kāḷasilā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu. "
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” replied those mendicants, and did as he asked. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:5.6"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā tañca rattiṃ tañca divāvasesaṃ gijjhakūṭe pabbate vihāsi. "
msgstr "Meanwhile, the Buddha spent the rest of that night and day on Vulture’s Peak Mountain. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:5.7"
msgid "Atha kho dve devatāyo abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ gijjhakūṭaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu … pe … ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. "
msgstr "Then, late at night, two glorious deities, lighting up the entire Vulture’s Peak, went up to the Buddha, bowed, and stood to one side. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:5.8"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho ekā devatā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "One deity said to him, "

msgctxt "sn22.87:5.9"
msgid "“vakkali, bhante, bhikkhu vimokkhāya cetetī”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, the mendicant Vakkali is intent on liberation!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:5.10"
msgid "Aparā devatā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "And another deity said to him, "

msgctxt "sn22.87:5.11"
msgid "“so hi nūna, bhante, suvimutto vimuccissatī”ti. "
msgstr "“He’ll definitely be well-freed!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:5.12"
msgid "Idamavocuṃ tā devatāyo. "
msgstr "This is what those deities said. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:5.13"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then they bowed and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on their right side, before vanishing right there. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn22.87:6.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā tassā rattiyā accayena bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then, when the night had passed, the Buddha addressed the mendicants: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:6.2"
msgid "“etha tumhe, bhikkhave, yena vakkali bhikkhu tenupasaṅkamatha; upasaṅkamitvā vakkaliṃ bhikkhuṃ evaṃ vadetha: "
msgstr "“Come, mendicants, go to the mendicant Vakkali and tell him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.122, sc7
msgctxt "sn22.87:7.1"
msgid "‘Suṇāvuso tvaṃ, vakkali, bhagavato vacanaṃ dvinnañca devatānaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Vakkali, hear the word of the Buddha and two deities. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:7.2"
msgid "Imaṃ, āvuso, rattiṃ dve devatāyo abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ gijjhakūṭaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. "
msgstr "Late last night, two glorious deities, lighting up the entire Vulture’s Peak, went up to the Buddha, bowed, and stood to one side. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:7.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho, āvuso, ekā devatā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "One deity said to him, "

# NOTE: MS lack quotes, but here it is double-nested.
msgctxt "sn22.87:7.4"
msgid "vakkali, bhante, bhikkhu vimokkhāya cetetīti. "
msgstr "“Sir, the mendicant Vakkali is intent on liberation!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:7.5"
msgid "Aparā devatā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "And another deity said to him, "

msgctxt "sn22.87:7.6"
msgid "so hi nūna, bhante, suvimutto vimuccissatīti. "
msgstr "“He’ll definitely be well-freed!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:7.7"
msgid "Bhagavā ca taṃ, āvuso vakkali, evamāha—"
msgstr "And the Buddha said, "

msgctxt "sn22.87:7.8"
msgid "mā bhāyi, vakkali; "
msgstr "“Do not fear, Vakkali, "

msgctxt "sn22.87:7.9"
msgid "mā bhāyi, vakkali. "
msgstr "do not fear! "

msgctxt "sn22.87:7.10"
msgid "Apāpakaṃ te maraṇaṃ bhavissati, apāpikā kālakiriyā’”ti. "
msgstr "Your death will not be a bad one; your passing will not be a bad one.”’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:7.11"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paṭissutvā yenāyasmā vakkali tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ vakkaliṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” those monks replied. They went to Vakkali and said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:7.12"
msgid "“suṇāvuso vakkali, bhagavato vacanaṃ dvinnañca devatānan”ti. "
msgstr "“Vakkali, hear the word of the Buddha and two deities.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.123, sc8
msgctxt "sn22.87:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā vakkali upaṭṭhāke āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then Vakkali addressed his carers, "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.2"
msgid "“etha maṃ, āvuso, mañcakā oropetha. "
msgstr "“Please, reverends, help me off my cot. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.3"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma mādiso ucce āsane nisīditvā tassa bhagavato sāsanaṃ sotabbaṃ maññeyyā”ti. "
msgstr "It’s unthinkable for one like me to listen to the Buddha’s instructions sitting on a high seat.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:8.4"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato vakkalissa paṭissutvā āyasmantaṃ vakkaliṃ mañcakā oropesuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” replied those mendicants, and helped him off his cot. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.5"
msgid "“Imaṃ, āvuso, rattiṃ dve devatāyo abhikkantāya rattiyā … pe … ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. "
msgstr "They repeated what the Buddha had said. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.6"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho, āvuso, ekā devatā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.7"
msgid "‘vakkali, bhante, bhikkhu vimokkhāya cetetī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.8"
msgid "Aparā devatā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.9"
msgid "‘so hi nūna, bhante, suvimutto vimuccissatī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.10"
msgid "Bhagavā ca taṃ, āvuso vakkali, evamāha: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.11"
msgid "‘mā bhāyi, vakkali; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.12"
msgid "mā bhāyi, vakkali. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.13"
msgid "Apāpakaṃ te maraṇaṃ bhavissati, apāpikā kālakiriyā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:8.14"
msgid "“Tena hāvuso, mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vandatha: "
msgstr " Vakkali said, “Well then, reverends, in my name bow with your head to the Buddha’s feet. Say to him: "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.15"
msgid "‘vakkali, bhante, bhikkhu ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno. "
msgstr "‘Sir, the mendicant Vakkali is sick, suffering, gravely ill. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.16"
msgid "So bhagavato pāde sirasā vandatī’ti. "
msgstr "He bows with his head to your feet.’ "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.17"
msgid "Evañca vadetha: "
msgstr "And then say: "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.18"
msgid "‘rūpaṃ aniccaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Form is impermanent. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.19"
msgid "Tāhaṃ, bhante, na kaṅkhāmi. "
msgstr "I have no doubt of that. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.20"
msgid "Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhanti na vicikicchāmi. "
msgstr "I’m certain that what is impermanent is suffering. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.21"
msgid "Yadaniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, natthi me tattha chando vā rāgo vā pemaṃ vāti na vicikicchāmi. "
msgstr "And I’m certain that I have no desire or greed or fondness for what is impermanent, suffering, and perishable. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:8.22"
msgid "Vedanā aniccā. "
msgstr "Feeling is impermanent … "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.23"
msgid "Tāhaṃ, bhante, na kaṅkhāmi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.24"
msgid "Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhanti na vicikicchāmi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.25"
msgid "Yadaniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, natthi me tattha chando vā rāgo vā pemaṃ vāti na vicikicchāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:8.26"
msgid "Saññā … "
msgstr "Perception is impermanent … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:8.27"
msgid "saṅkhārā aniccā. "
msgstr "Choices are impermanent … "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.28"
msgid "Tāhaṃ, bhante, na kaṅkhāmi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.29"
msgid "Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhanti na vicikicchāmi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.30"
msgid "Yadaniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, natthi me tattha chando vā rāgo vā pemaṃ vāti na vicikicchāmi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:8.31"
msgid "Viññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ. "
msgstr "Consciousness is impermanent. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.32"
msgid "Tāhaṃ, bhante, na kaṅkhāmi. "
msgstr "I have no doubt of that. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.33"
msgid "Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhanti na vicikicchāmi. "
msgstr "I’m certain that what is impermanent is suffering. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.34"
msgid "Yadaniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, natthi me tattha chando vā rāgo vā pemaṃ vāti na vicikicchāmī’”ti. "
msgstr "And I’m certain that I have no desire or greed or fondness for what is impermanent, suffering, and perishable.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:8.35"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato vakkalissa paṭissutvā pakkamiṃsu. "
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” those monks replied, and left. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:8.36"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā vakkali acirapakkantesu tesu bhikkhūsu satthaṃ āharesi. "
msgstr "And then, not long after those mendicants had left, Venerable Vakkali slit his wrists. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn22.87:9.1"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then those senior mendicants went up to the Buddha and told him Vakkali’s message. "

msgctxt "sn22.87:9.2"
msgid "“vakkali, bhante, bhikkhu ābādhiko dukkhito bāḷhagilāno; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:9.3"
msgid "so bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:9.4"
msgid "evañca vadeti: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:9.5"
msgid "‘rūpaṃ aniccaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:9.6"
msgid "Tāhaṃ, bhante, na kaṅkhāmi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:9.7"
msgid "Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhanti na vicikicchāmi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:9.8"
msgid "Yadaniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, natthi me tattha chando vā rāgo vā pemaṃ vāti na vicikicchāmi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:9.9"
msgid "Vedanā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:9.10"
msgid "saññā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:9.11"
msgid "saṅkhārā … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:9.12"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:9.13"
msgid "Tāhaṃ, bhante, na kaṅkhāmi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:9.14"
msgid "Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhanti na vicikicchāmi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.87:9.15"
msgid "Yadaniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, natthi me tattha chando vā rāgo vā pemaṃ vāti na vicikicchāmī’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn22.87:10.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to the mendicants, "

msgctxt "sn22.87:10.2"
msgid "“āyāma, bhikkhave, yena isigilipassaṃ kāḷasilā tenupasaṅkamissāma; "
msgstr "“Come, mendicants, let’s go to the Black Rock on the slopes of Isigili, "

msgctxt "sn22.87:10.3"
msgid "yattha vakkalinā kulaputtena satthamāharitan”ti. "
msgstr "where Vakkali, the gentleman, slit his wrists.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:10.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:10.5"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ yena isigilipassaṃ kāḷasilā tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha together with several mendicants went to the Black Rock on the slopes of Isigili. "

# NOTE: See discussion https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/turning-shoulders-and-casting-off-aggregates/2949
msgctxt "sn22.87:10.6"
msgid "Addasā kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ vakkaliṃ dūratova mañcake vivattakkhandhaṃ semānaṃ. "
msgstr "The Buddha saw Vakkali off in the distance lying on his cot, having cast off the aggregates. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.124, sc11
msgctxt "sn22.87:11.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena dhūmāyitattaṃ timirāyitattaṃ gacchateva purimaṃ disaṃ, gacchati pacchimaṃ disaṃ, gacchati uttaraṃ disaṃ, gacchati dakkhiṇaṃ disaṃ, gacchati uddhaṃ disaṃ, gacchati adho disaṃ, gacchati anudisaṃ. "
msgstr "Now at that time a cloud of black smoke was moving east, west, north, south, above, below, and in-between. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:11.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "The Buddha said to the mendicants, "

msgctxt "sn22.87:11.3"
msgid "“passatha no tumhe, bhikkhave, etaṃ dhūmāyitattaṃ timirāyitattaṃ gacchateva purimaṃ disaṃ … pe … gacchati anudisan”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, do you see that cloud of black smoke moving east, west, north, south, above, below, and in-between?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:11.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.87:11.5"
msgid "“Eso kho, bhikkhave, māro pāpimā vakkalissa kulaputtassa viññāṇaṃ samanvesati: "
msgstr "“That’s Māra the Wicked searching for Vakkali’s consciousness, wondering: "

msgctxt "sn22.87:11.6"
msgid "‘kattha vakkalissa kulaputtassa viññāṇaṃ patiṭṭhitan’ti? "
msgstr "‘Where is Vakkali’s consciousness established?’ "

msgctxt "sn22.87:11.7"
msgid "Appatiṭṭhitena ca, bhikkhave, viññāṇena vakkali kulaputto parinibbuto”ti. "
msgstr "But since his consciousness is not established, Vakkali is extinguished.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.87:11.8"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

